\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Your dad just ignored it if it happened when he was home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you remember any particular occasion when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 got}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  sent to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 I can tell you that the only time I got a hiding off me f
ather, it was - we lived at South Shields and - there was a good big grocer's shop, Holborn's, I can remember it yet, on the corner, Southend Street and Barnes Road, and - well lads in them days, we used to be in - one street was fighting another street, 
you know, gangs. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 We were fighting Barnes Road this night and I threw stone, it went through }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Holman's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  shop window. And - somebody went and told me father and he came out and looked for us. And I got a hiding, put to bed that night, that's only time me father ever hit me in his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I thought it was terrible at the time. Because we were only fighting the gangs you know. I thought I was defending myself really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Would you say you got the ideas about how you should behave from both your parents or was one of them more important than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh, just me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You think she was more important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. But - me father - he had no influence on my life at all and yet - I could do anything with me father. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Me mother used to just say skulky, they always called me skulky, I don't know why but I was always skulky. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Out the was skulky, see if you can get your dad to come home. Get your father to come home. And I used to go down the bars and - used to find him i
n the bars. Come home. No, I - I'll be up when I'm ready. And I've seen 'em go to school and come back and still he's not home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you get any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I got lit
tle bits of presents. Me mam used to generally give me something. Me, father were a shilling. Always got a shilling - off me father. I don't know whether you could call that a present or not but - I got a shilling, that's - but as for articles of presents
 we never - got none.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you get anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Never invited anyone to a little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 tea party}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Anything special that you did with your mother and father on Christmas day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, just - on the morning I can r
emember when we first got up, what presents and that and we used to take them all into their bedroom, used to take them all into their bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was your father always in that day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Christmas morning he was, yes. Aye, he was always in Christmas mo
rning. And - we used to take our toys in there and - of course too much, used to chase up and - he used to get up and play with us Christmas morning. All our toys and that you know. He mother hadn't time 'cos she was getting - the goose and that ready.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you do anything else together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, just a - just a day general enjoyment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were there any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Not a one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Nobody could play anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. We had a piano. I had a piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Who played that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Nobody was playing it at the time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was there anyone who used to sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Apart from Christmas Day did your mother or father ever play any games with you or the other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well there was two or three, I think I've got some of them yet, three - was the Mohicans is it? Last of the Mohicans, that's it. One - one or two like that we got. We hadn't lot of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How many would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh, I don't think there'd be a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 dozen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you have any newspapers in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Oh I don't think so, I can't remember. We never had no time to read newspapers actually, just had such a terrible time at work. She was a sick woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So you don't remember any regular papers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Weeklies or evening papers or Sunday papers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Sunday papers we used to get. I remember News of the world. We used to get the News of the World every Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I think that's about the only one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you ever get magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you remember your mother or father ever reading, apart from the News of the World?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Me mother read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What did she used to read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Just the books that she got off the neighbours downstairs, these little women's books you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you remember any titles of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were they stories or magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, weekly things they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Something like Woman's Own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, something like and - they're periodical things really, get them every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 But she used to borrow them off the neighbours?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
We used to - we used to get them from the lady downstairs, from a neighbours family. Yes, Beano, Comic Cuts I can remember what we used to get, but we never bought any, we always used to get them from the Levis's downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your mother or father ever read to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 The first funeral I can ever remember was me grandfather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I'd only be - ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Who went to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 There was me father and me brother Bill and I. We came from South Shields up to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  and - I can remember it was a terrible - it teemed. And me brother and I sat with the driver 
on the - the horse vehicle in them days, there was no motors or anything you know and we thought it was great sitting up with the driver at the funeral. We got soaking wet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was there only three of you there altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh no, there was all me father's - me grandfather's family, his wife and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What kind of clothes did the people wear who went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 They wore all black, I can remember every - everybody was in black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Everything black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you wear black as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, we just had black overcoats on. Because we - we - we never wore ties or anything, we just had these white collars you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did people have top hats on, black hats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 They had hats - there was no top hats. Bowler hats as you call them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did the people have armbands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Armbands. Black armbands on. And - I can remember when people went to the funerals from Stannock Street. And went to the general hospital - and must have picked the body up there. And he was buried In }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Anzac}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  cemetery. 'Course 
I didn't know - at the time where I was, after you, 'cos we were just young from South Shields so, but I - now I can remember - I can picture it - since then I've pictured all this - it happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your mother ever take you out to visit neighbours or friends or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I used to sometimes go and stop with me brother's brothers - like me uncles. In }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 , often used to go and stop with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 But did your mother or father ever take you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You just used to go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 go on me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you make any visit at all with your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were you ever taken shopping by your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Always she wanted to go with her shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You used to go with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Anybody else with you or just the two of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Just the two 'cos I was the eldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How far away from home did you go to the shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - when we were at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  we lived Arches Street and we used to the bottom of Arches Street to the store an
d I can remember one day I was doing something in this store which I shouldn't have been doing and the chap came running after me with a big knife. And - I thought he was going to cut me head off as he said he was going to do you know and I put me hands u
p. By God, had to take us to hospital.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did he cut your fingers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh did it, aye, had to take us to hospital.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I bet he was sorry about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Aye, I can - I can remember these things very vivid - memory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was it deep cuts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh y
es. Aye. There's still the marks there yet, look, see. Both hands see, he was going to cut my head off. You know, I expected the chap just carried on. And I - oh I was going to - I was saving my face. You see how simple things happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you ever go out just with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
No. The only time I was with father was when I went to look for him. And this time when we came to me grandfather's funeral, were with him that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you ever go anywhere else with either your mother or your father
 or both of them, for example, at Bank Holidays, did you ever have any trips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. Just if we - tell you as I used to go up to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 . To me Uncle Tom's and me Uncle Bob's or - they were me father's two brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How long did you spend with Uncle Tom and Uncle Bob?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh just a weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you do that regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did any of your brothers or sisters go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. No, I was only one ever done it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What did you do whilst you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I used to go a lot with me Uncle Bob and me Uncle Tom to the barriers, they were great harriers in them days and I used to go with them.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were these men running?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Men running, yes. Well they were just young men them days like, I were just a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 kiddy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 . But I used to go and potter round with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you tell me how you used to spend your Saturdays in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  before your mother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, just kicking round and playing football and that. We used to get errands, 
what errands there was to be done. And - do what we had to do in the home. If there was any cleaning up or anything like that - anything that had to be done, then the day was your own once you got that done, you could just go and please yourself. We somet
imes went to Burnt Closes or got down to Wilton Cut, anywhere, you know, like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What's Burnt Closes and Wilton Cut?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well Wilton Cut's part of the River Tyne. Where there was boats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about Burnt Closes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well it's - it's a done. The River Burn flows through it, it's tributary of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Tyne}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  like. But it's all hilly, you know, it's down in a valley. It was lovely to play, cowboys and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Indians}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  we used to play in them days and I used to be the old trestle bridge over it where the railway
 used to run from the pit. Of course you used to climb all over, oh we used to have a grand time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about Sundays, how did you spend Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Just playing about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 We had to go to Sunday school first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 In the morning or afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And afternoon. Then we - you had to come home and take your best clothes off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What were your best clothes like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Little suit, like a little suit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Short trousers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Short - oh short trousers, by heavens. I wasn't a
llowed long trousers when I was working man. No. I wasn't allowed long trousers, about sixteen before I got long trousers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your parents think it was wrong to work or to play any games on Sundays or didn't they mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, don't seem to mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your parents go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Me mother did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Which church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What was it called -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was it a Catholic church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was your dad Church of England as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How often did she go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh me mother used to go pretty often. Sunday evening. Was about the only time she actually could go. And sometimes she took us with her.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your dad ever go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. Dad go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You just went now and again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You always went to Sunday school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh always had to go to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you remember any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 We used to go to Wryton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How did you travel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 On a brake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Used to be a horse drawn -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Like a bus?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Aye. Just maybe twelve or fourteen sitting either side of the brake and there were two horses on. We used to go to Wryton in this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Once a year. By heavens. Once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was there any other social activities organised by the church that you went to, by the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, there wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What did you do in connection with the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Just used to do our singing and practices.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How often were the practices?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Three times a week. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And you used to sing every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 At Sunday school and in the church as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Not 'til I got older.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did it have any temperance clubs attached to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you belong to any other club organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Who taught you to say your prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you ever have family prayers, all the family together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your father take any interest in politics can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well I - I didn't know really what politics was but - were Liberals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 He was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Yes. And - and we had to be Liberals. Then - I remember - on two elections used to be a - they called the Liberal agent Mr Robson. And we used to mak
e paper balls on end of a string you know, wrap paper up on the end of a string. We used to go, vote, vote, vote for Mr Robson. We used to go in the streets, look for the - for the Tories, we used to have some right old scraps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was this before you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes, oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you know why your dad was a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Because his father was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about your mother, did she have any interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was she a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I don't know but she never had any interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You never heard her say anything about politics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you remember your father voting in any election before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I don't know whether he voted. See, because we were actually too young and we didn't see anything of his life practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you know if your mother voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 She had her chance at the end of the war, do you know if she did then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I don't know, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 But you think if your dad had voted he would have voted Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
In some firms men felt they were running a bit of a risk if they voted for one party and they knew their bosses voted for another, do you think your fad felt any kind of pressure because of whatever his employers wanted him to vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well I don't know about that but I can tell you from my own experience. When I was fourteen - everybody was wondering what I was going to do. See, me grandfather, he was foreman plumber, the North Eastern Marine. Me father had been foreman boiler mak
er at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 Slipway and - me two uncles - they were all shipyard men. And it was naturally thought that I was going into shipyard. See, well - I didn't want to go, I didn't want anything to do with shipyard. 'Cos it meant if I worked in the shipyard I w
as going to have to travel to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
. That was one of the things that - you know at the time. I was going to work at pit because all the lads I was working with worked at the pit. And I went in the pits in 1914. But I can remember - where - as soon as I 
started the pit, the first week I was at the pit, chap came to me and - join the union. But you hadn't to tell anybody. You hadn't to tell anybody, you were - in the union. As soon if they knew you were in the union you'd get the sack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Because they knew you'd be voting Liberal or Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh well if you were in the union you weren't allowed to vote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Liberal}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 . By God. That was a - a crime. And even in the later years I came up to the United here in 19 - 1929 and - I got a job them at -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you know if your father was a member of the Liberal party, did he actually join?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, no, he was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did he work for the Liberal party at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did either your father or mother take any interest in politics apart from at election times, did they ever do anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well I wouldn't like to say for sure because I was too - I - I know me father didn't. Because - the only thing me father had time for was work and beer. He had no time for home. Never mind politics, he had n
o time for home. In the two wars the pubs was open from half past six in the morning 'til twelve o'clock at night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So as far as you're dads concerned, when he wasn't working he was drinking? When he wasn't drinking he was working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 That's all it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about your mother when she wasn't working, how did she relax?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Oh, me mother never relaxed. She had - six were as you could say all very young and she he had the whole - look after everything, home and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So she didn't have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 She had no home life, no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did she have any friends or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh she had friends. The Levis's downstairs and - different people in the street you know., she would talk out of doors but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Never went out. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How many evenings a week would your father spend at home, one, or less than one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - you could depend upon him being home on a Sunday night. And a Saturday night. Saturday night, they
 never worked Saturday night and Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So he was often home those two nights?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
But it was - meant that - in the morning before he came home you see because the pubs didn't chuck out 'til twelve and unless V could go and tell him to come out he was sat there and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your father attend any clubs or pubs, did he attend regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 He lived in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did he ever take your mother with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was he keen on any kind of sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well not that I can remember, he - he - he never took any interest in anything man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You can't remember him going to any races for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh he never - go to races or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did he ever have a bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well I don't know outside - we - I never knew what h
e done outside. I don't think he troubled much about horses though mind. He wasn't that type of man, not a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 horsy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your mother or father belong to any savings clubs, sick clubs or funeral clubs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Insurances. Had all insured like. In fact I'm still paying insurances now mother took up for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How much do you pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Penny a week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you remember anything else that they paid into?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I think that would be all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Smashing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was there any one brother or sister that you felt very close to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
No. We were all - our Bill and I see were - two lads, were the two oldest. We used to go about more - but - I used to play more with the lads down hill than I did with our Bill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So as a child you played with your neighbours more than your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Jackie Levis downstairs, he lived downstairs. He was me favourite. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Where did you used to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Anywhere where there's trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Would you say mainly in the street or mainly out in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 fields}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 In the fields, there was - you played very little in the streets, them days. Plenty of room to play in the fields and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What kind of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh just t
he same thing lads play today, football - walking on tin blocks you know, on strings and stilts and things like that and it was - you had to be because there wasn't the enjoyment like there is today. I - I can remember - one time went up to Jarold Slacks,
 
I don't know where Jarold Slacks is. Well it's between - it' Just outside of South Shields, it was - it's - it's part of the river but it's very shallow and used to season all the timber there. You know, all these big wood merchants, they used to - oh tho
u
sands and thousands of - logs and things. They used to make them into rafts, see rope them altogether so they didn't drift away. And they were just left in the water for years like that. Well it was a great playground for us. We used to - and - there was 
o
ne day we were playing and our Bill, me brother, was with us. And I slipped and I went underneath this raft. And I didn't know this until later but me father had come home, he was passing in the tramcar. And he said, I've just seen somebody's lad drowned.
 
Well I don't know who - I don't know who got us out yet but they got us out and they got us - I'm still here. But that was the thing, what your father went and told you, I've seen somebody's lad drowned. You know, that was the things we used to get up to.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were you allowed to get as dirty as you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your mother fuss you about getting dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh she used to - shove you like but - she never thrashed you or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So you didn't feel you had to keep clean all the time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. By heavens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your mother and father let you play with anyone that you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Yes. Not unless - anybody that - I expect they must have heard - sometimes we were told, don't - there used to be a lad, Tommy Kublick, and I can remember the name yet, I hadn't to play with Tommy Kublick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Anybody else that you can think of that you weren't allowed to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh there was various times, different times, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you know why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You never knew why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you belong to any clubs of any kind, any youth clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Boy Scouts. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were you in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 boy scouts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  for a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well right when I was fourteen, when I started work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Up until you were fourteen did you have any hobbies of any kind, did you keep any pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, never kept pets or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you collect cigarette cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Collected cigarette cards. Oh cigarette cards. God, we had thousands and thousan
ds of them. I give them away now to the grandchildren. Aye, I kept them all these times. We had sets as we called them you know. We used to go on all over swapping, you know, any swaps. And I had tram cards, birds, cricketers, football - oh, I had all - a
nd it's only recently I give them all away to grand - my grandchildren.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Anything else in the way of hobbies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Just the Scouts, I liked the Boy Scouts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Not - not in me younger days, later on I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - nothing much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I couldn't get a bicycle. We used to like to ride on a bike. We never had one of our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about sports, were you very keen on any special sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I would say I was a good all-rounder. When I was in the Boy Scouts I went in for everything that was going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What was going, what kind of things did you do, football I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - walking and running. Anything that was going in Scouts or at school and - I was a good all-rounder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you ever go to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 To any concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 If we got a treat to the cinema, what - you'd think you are a lord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So you'd been once or twice?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh been - once or twice -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 While you were sill young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. Used to pay a ha'penny on Saturday morning to get in and you got a bag of sweets and a comic for your ha'penny. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you get any pocket money then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Where did you get your ha'pennies from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Empty bottles, anything was paying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did anybody outside the home ever help your mother to look after the house or the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No one, like your gran didn't come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Or neighbours or anything? Did she get any help at all ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well not that I never seen any - Mrs Levis downstairs she used to come up just like neighbours but they never used to expect to - they would help each other out but nothing to what we - would take any notice of, nothing - nothing exceptional.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What happened if your mother was ill or she had to stay in bed, how did the family manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I can never remember mother being ill. The only time when she used to go to hospital to have the baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Me grandmother used to come from South Shields. But never me father's people. He - because me father was the black sheep of the family. Me father was the black sheep of the family. Because - in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  Madisons, household name. Oh but it's just - it's
 not so recently we had had - she died and she was the head nurse you know for the whole borough and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And important family then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh they're all great Freemasons. I remember when I started work, went down, down a street to South Shields there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Where were the nearest relatives on your father's side, to where you lived when you were in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 ? Were they very close?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well, ten minutes away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about your mother's relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 South Shields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How long did it take to get across to where your grandmother lived, from your house to her house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well sometimes used to get there, we used to go down to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 , to the boat landing and went in a boat, it was threepence in the boat. Down to South }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Shields}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 . It used to take about half an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You say your mother's friend was the neighbour downstairs, they used to meet in each other's homes I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh always in and out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your mother have any other friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Not that I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about your dad, who were his mates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh he had all his workmates. He never used to bring anybody home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did he got on well with the family downstairs as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh he were - him and Joe Levis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So he was friendly with the father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Joey Levis is as big a boozer as him I think but not as bad like but he was a good boozer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So your mother and father really shared friends with that family didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 them
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, that's - they were practically the only friends we had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 . What - what we knew of you see because we were just youngsters.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did they ever meet altogether, all four of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Always the women or the men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And the men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So there was no one who was ever invited into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, no. There was never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Apart from this woman who used to come up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Apart from Mrs Levis she'd come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 When she came up did she have something to drink or eat, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 We never have - beer - father wouldn't allow beer in the house. For he's such a drinker, wouldn't allow drink in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So what did you drink in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Water and lemonade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 This woman from downstairs, what did she get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh - tea. Tea. My mother used to sit tea, tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did this woman used to cal in casually quite often without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Two of them used to ask, they used to walk - when you're not coming in. We used to go the same, we used to just run straight in their house and - never knocked and asked could you go in, we just used to run in and they used to just the same in ours.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were there other neighbours who used to come in or was it just this one family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh - it was only this one family that we were so friendly with. We used to go in other people's houses mind, yo
ungsters, you know what youngsters are, but me mother never used to go much mind. She went downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
What do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends or their neighbours, when they used to be all together? Did your mother ever go down to see this family in the evening and stay there for an hour or so?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. No, I can never once remember me mother ever going out and leaving me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So were there any other occasions when your father and mother met people that you know of apart from the Levis's when they used to come up?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
No, because we - there was none of me father's people used to come visiting us. And me mother's mother lived at South shields, her husband was dead and she never used to come up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 A lot of peop
le divide society into different social classes or groups, taking the period before 1918, did you think of some people belonging to one class and some belonging to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - up to about fourteen or fifteen I wouldn't say I had noticed because I
 - I was too young really. But after - fourteen, fifteen, I did notice, there was a distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What different groups did you notice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well in the church especially. There was one crowd seemed a better-off crowd in the church, and they stuck to 
themselves. And - and that still goes today. There's nothing going to change my opinion on that. There's a certain clique gets together and they - they all seem as though they're all in that same one standard of life. Not that I have anything against them
 anything. But it's just that - we seem as though we are - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 better}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 status of life than what you are. See. My husband works in office, you're husband's only a bus driver. So - we are better than what you are. You see, I've found that is entirely true. Even - 
we were got a house in Nunsmore Road here in 1940 when we came to live up here, a lovely house, it was too big for what we wanted, belonged to one of the - the Richardsons, the shipyard people you know, one of their daughters. And the house was to let and
 
I hunted Newcastle high and low for a house and - I seen this bill in To Let in the window and we got this house. I'd only been in the house two weeks when the people right opposite were - they moved out of their house because there's a bus driver came to
 
live in this street. And that's - and Mr Edwards as was one of Directors on the Newcastle Board of Education and he openly told them, he says, the place is deteriorating, he says, getting bus drivers coming into the street now to live. And - you can only 
speak from actual fact. And this is an actual fact. A Director of Education with such a thing in his head and you cannot understand it man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Going back to the time just after you started work, did you think of the people just being in these two groups t
hen, the better-off and the others or did you think there were more than two groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well - not - when I first started I did notice, but I - I wouldn't say they were better-off. But - I look at it - it's friendly, friendliness. See, that's the only w
ay I look on life. I don't consider wealth or anything to be - the only thing you get out of life is what you put into it to me. And friendliness is a whole life. And if I've no friendliness with anyone well - to me I've no life. Irrespective if they've g
ot a hundred or a thousand or -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So you group people according to how friendly they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And you think there were probably two groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh definitely was. There still is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Which group would you say you belonged to in 1915 to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh well I - I was in the lower group. The bottom group.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What sort of people belonged to the same group as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - rank and file of the working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 All your neighbours, all your own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - I'll not
 say all my own neighbours because that was people in the church and that's where I found it more so than anywhere else. I found it more in the church than anywhere. It's a - it's a - it's a nasty thing to say about a church because a church is a place wh
ere, if there's any friendliness at all it should be there. But to me it's - it's more distinct in the church than anywhere. Even in - where we are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What sort of people belonged to the other classes or groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well I - I don't really know whi
ch way to put them, how you - to me it's just an opinion I have of themselves. They really think they're better than somebody else because they're - my husband works in an office, see, you're husband only works in a supermarket. And you think that they're
 a class higher than anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 When you first thought about this when you first started work did you think of office workers as being of a high class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes, definitely they were. As we call them the collar and tie }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 brigade}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 . They would never speak to the - such as us. The canteen - had a canteen of their own. Distinction was made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were there any other people that you can say were of that kind?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh well I can only say for what I worked with. See when you get up the higher class well 
we never see much of them but for the actual working class, yes, they did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 their selves}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 , divide themselves into classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were you ever taught to curtsey or touch your cap or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Who to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Elders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Didn't matter who they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 To - to all your elders and such as the - the Vicar, a doctor, anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about your dad's workmates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh well, wouldn't have to see much of them. The only time I see them was in the bar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Would you touch your cap to them I the bar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 But you would to the doctor and the vicar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And you said anyone older than yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Your elders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you mean when they came into your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Yes. You were always told if anybody elder give 'em your seat anywhere anything like that. You get up and - you always respect your elders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was there a difference 
between a doctor who is an elder of yours and a coalminer who's an elder of yours, did you give one more respect that the other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well I - I wouldn't say you'd give more respect. You - you made more show by lifting your hat at the doctor but you woul
dn't - say as your mate in the coalmine. But yet you'd have as much respect for the man in the coalmine as you had for the doctor. Maybe more. But it was as you were taught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 When you were a boy was there anybody that you had to call sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Just the schoolmaster. The schoolteacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No one else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 The vicar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What did you call him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Just those two, the schoolteacher and the vicar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And the vicar and the doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - we didn't have any doings with any other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you remember anybody showing respect to your parents in these says, anyone saying sir or madam to your father or mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Who were considered the most important people in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Most important. Well the only one which is important was - the councillors, the J.P. If you wanted anything signing, anything, you always went to these people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 The town council men you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 The town councilor, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 There was no one person or two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I wouldn't say so. Even the mayor was just an ordinary working man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you meet these people, these councilors, did you know them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you recognize them in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Why do you think councillors and J.P's were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well I don't know, it was just the position they were given I think. Once he got his position. They - they had the authority to sign what nobody else could. If you wanted a form or 
anything signed you went to a doctor, J.P. See well anybody couldn't sign those things which nowadays a lot of people can sign these things now for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Who did shopkeepers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well I couldn't say anything of their private lives but they were very friendly when you went into their shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And the clergymen? Did they seem to stick with themselves or did they mix with doctors or shopkeepers or miners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - I would say that they mixed with a certain class. They didn't do what
 they're supposed to do. Not in my opinion. Because there was nobody loved the church any more than I did. And that's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 of the things that turned me against - well I didn't turn against church but it certainly didn't help me with the church. In a church 
there was a clique, and if you weren't in that clique you was well be out. It didn't matter what your circumstances were, there was some very influential people but they weren't in this clique..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So the clergymen had a group of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh - even
 - in my own church at South Shields - had a young curate there he came - he came and he was a fine fellow. And he used to have - he formed this sort of Boy Scouts, we had a brass band and - we had a grand troop. And he used to have twenty-five lads to te
a every Saturday. But there was twenty of those lads was there every Saturday. Every Saturday there's twenty of the same lads was there. He - he was the Scout master and the curate of the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And he had his favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh definitely had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were they the sons of the people in the clique?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Oh yes. Oh by heavens, yes. If your father - if you - your father wasn't in the clique you weren't. Wasn't worth going to church. Like me, I was only one-might get an invitation once a year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about schoolteachers, were they somewhat similar in their friends and their associates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well - couldn't really say because we hadn't much to do with their private lives. Yes, you - you met more of the clergyman see every day but schoolteachers once it was half past four they're away, you never see them no more 'til nine o'clock next morning.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about employers, the bossed generally in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well I found that they definitely are a class of their own. And they make you know that when y
ou've got to go and see them for interview or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 By doing what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Letting you see what - what authority they have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you give me an example, a time when you went for an interview and some of the things that were said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes. When I started on the buses here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 This is a bit outside the period isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, 1926.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you think of any examples up to 1918, right when you first started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 See mostly when we were lads - you - you - you're new into the job and
 you're doing anything - you daren't question anybody. So you're more or less - do that. And you had no - you daren't say, no, or - you daren't even to back answer them in them days. See you had no leg to stand on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 It's not until you get older that you realize you've got rights?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Would you say there was any difference between the people who went to the Church of England church, the Methodist and Congregational chapel and the Catholic church when you were either in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 
Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  or in South Shields before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I - the only thing that I found is the - the Catholics is more clannish.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 The Catholics think they're better - more than anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Stick together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 But the other two groups are similar are they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 They're - friendly people but they don't stick as the Catholics do. I - I don't know whether you can gather what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You often find Catholics who've got Catholic friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh by heavens, but if you're a Catholic you were a friend of theirs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Were there any differences between these religious groups in terms of income or employment, could you say that the Catholics were richer or poorer or had better jobs or worse jobs than any of the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I wouldn't say they'd any better jobs, I
'd just say they're all about the same because there's all walks of life. I wouldn't say the Catholics was any - better off than the Church of England anything. Because after all there's more Catholics in the world than anything and you all work for your 
living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different standards?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, all about the same. Yes, we're all about the same standard of living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you describe a ty
pical family in each of the two groups, the friendly ones as you describe them and the unfriendly ones, in the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh well the ones in the upper class didn't do - manual work, they always sent into better jobs. They were - that's about onl
y thing I would say that - a fellow was a decent job going it was the better class that got it. The average working man's family didn't get that chance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did any of these groups feel superior to the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. Well the - the better class as we called them, the middle class, they - they were a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 aloof}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 . They would have nothing to do with the working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You think they thought they were superior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Definitely they did, that was definite.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did the working class not feel superior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You couldn't. You couldn't, you hadn't the means to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Could you think of the families around where you lived, of any that you would describe as being rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How do you mean rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Scruffy, disreputable, noisy, dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 All of us really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Any particular families that stand out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Tell me about one of the worst examples?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well the - the lad that used to sit next to me in the school desk, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Emlyn}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Hughes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 A }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Welshman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I don't know what he was but that was his name, Emlyn Hughes. And he - he was absolutely lifting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What do you mean lifting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Bugs. They were crawling about his clothes. And - I told the teacher. I - I never told the teacher first, I told me mother when I went home. And she says, well you ought to tell the teacher. And they had to take him away. He was that bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you know his family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 His family lived - Osborne Terrace in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  they lived, we knew where they lived. But his father was shipyard worker, same as me father and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Why do you think he was so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well he'd been neglected, the home has, there's been dirt in the house, that's the only place where bugs and them things come from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were there lots of families like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I wouldn't say lots but that was an example. There would be some like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you think of others that you would call bad families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Bad families - meaning getting in trouble - mischief. That lad I hadn't to play with I told you, Tommy Kublick. They were always in tro
uble. In - in police, they were in police court, yes, were in police often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you think of some families round about there who you would call respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well there was a few but I couldn't just think of their names you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you tell me something about them? What was it that made them respectable, what did they do or not do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well if they - their way of life. Help anybody that went to their church and in trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was there any distinction made between craftsmen on one hand and labourers on the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well after I started work I could tell you better but - before I started work I couldn't say much about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 When you first started work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How could you notice that there was the difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
In - in the first thing was the pay. The first thing was the pay. And - second thing was in work. That the craftsman had a say. And the - the unskilled man, he was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Nobody listened to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, well - not in them days especially. No
wadays, might have some say now. But in them days you hadn't. Because in them days the trade union movement were just beginning to find its feet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was this difference reflected in the home as well, away from their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 work}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 , in the streets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well I don
't know, just take me father, he was one of the top craftsmen in the - on the Tyne and he wasn't - he was nobody, he was - he wouldn't even join the Freemasons.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were some of the labourers in the Freemasons then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes. Oh aye, some of the - some labourers in Freemasons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So the distinction was at work really rather than at home you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 At work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your mother and your father have the same attitude to the people in the different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, me mother was more placid than me father was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What made your father upset then about the different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well he - he - he was more like I am. People that wants to be something which they're not - really not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 He's more against them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. He for - for all me fa
ther was what he was he detested anybody trying to make anything better themselves than what they really were. He used to detest that. He used to say for all he was - more drunk than what he was sober, after all, he says, we're all God's made us. He says,
 and we're all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular class or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I don't think me mother was - I - I don't know my mother - I think she'd be - left separate you know. What a life she had to lead.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 She hardly had time to grow up did she really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
We had no time at all. See when she was a young woman in her prime she was having kiddy after kiddy, kiddy after kiddy. Well she - and she had no relaxation. See, me father was never coming home. She would have all that worry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Was it possible in this period between 1906 and 1914 to move from one class to another, from being a labourer to being a doctor, that kind of move?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you not think of anyone who made any big moves like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. If - if you were a labourer your family was labourers because there was no chance in education and there's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 definitely}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  no money. Therefore it only rested if your father was - better off what we were your family got a better chance than what we got.
 Come home to that. But nowadays that's all changed. The education I mean is different, everybody does get a chance. All the children gets a chance now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, there was one of me father's pals, Tom Davidson, everybody spoke well - he was a - well spoken - well spoken of man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well he was - he was a - just a worker like me father, he worked at Slipway with me father.
 But he was a good man in his church, he used to go to his church three times of a Sunday, didn't touch liquor or anything. And he was very thrifty man. And everybody - he came to see me father and me father was dying and - and he came downstairs from the
 
room where me father was like after this, he see father was going and he says, now Joe, he says, don't think I'm trying to pry into your lives. He says, but how is your father - leaving you lads, 'cos there was only me brother and I left then. All our fam
ily died young. Yes. Except me sister Lily, she was twenty-one when she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 All the others died before they were twenty-one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 All the others - yes, all the other three died before they were twenty-one. And - I can remember Mr Davidson saying, do
n't think I'm trying to pry into your private affairs, he called us Joe, and he said, how is your father leaving you? Oh, I says, in debt. He says, eeh, he says, what a shame. He says, you know, he says, you lads should have been independent. He says, you
 
- for the money that your father has worked for, he says, you lads should never have had to work another day of your lives. He says, I haven't worked for a quarter of the money your father has worked for. He say, and I have a street of houses, which he as
, Davison Terrace, Rose Hill. He says, I have a street of houses now. Named after him. All his houses, yes, he had, all built.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So he was what you'd call a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 He - he did - he - he was, he - his actions and everything you know. He got
 labeled real gentleman. But he was just a workman she same as me father. But he was a different type of man to me father you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh - Bob Chambers, he was a policeman.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh - what did any kid think of a policeman? No, I used to think - he was a real cop, but in them days - oh he was a terror.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were you frightened of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Because he put fear into you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Wel
l the actions. If he caught you doing anything you'd get a clip around the lugs with his glove. He'd never - he'd never take you to court, it'd have to be something serious before he'd ever took anybody to court. And when you got a clip on the lug with th
ese gloves - you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 When you were naughty did your mother ever say, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Her often used to frighten me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did it frighten you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. We were already frightened of the policeman so - her telling us that made n
o difference because we were already afraid of the policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How do you think he treated other people, the adults that he had to deal with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well he seemed all right, he - I've seen take drunken men home. I've seen him take drunken men, rather t
han lock them up, he used to take them home. Yes, he was - he used to come up with men and play quoits and things you know, we use to play quoits in them days, you'll not know what quoits are. Rings and hobs at either end, three ends you know. But it used
 
to be the favourite pastime then, he used to come out and - but he - he was part of the - the - was part of the town where we lived really, that was his area. And he was looked on as a friend. No doubt he had times when he had to do his duty. But - I've s
een him take drunken men home before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was the house you lived in rented, the one in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Rented, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 The one in South Shields as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you ever see the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I couldn't tell you who the landlord was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you ever feel that your parents were having to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Me mother was always having to struggle. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What did you think about that at the time, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well as I got older I thought what a shame it was
 for money father was making. For all I'd to take three and four, sometimes five gold sovereigns home - it was - nothing to what me father was - what he couldn't drink all - that we're spending. It was lucky it was helping him. And - his home was sufferin
g for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You say you were taking home four or five gold sovereigns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How much did he earn then in a good week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh God only knows that, he would never tell anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Could you make a guess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh it must have been twenty or 
thirty pounds. Yes. Well - Mr Davidson told you he had a street of houses. He'd paid for having a street of houses built.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 This was in 1909 or 10 was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 But if he was sending five pounds home quite often it's not surprising is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
That was nothing to him. Five pounds. I've seen me after I've started work and I got in the pit and I got properly settled in, although I was making good money, I'm not afraid to - you hear people say what the miners got in these old days well was in the
 pits when pits was bad. And I made good money. And I've seen on Saturday me father's come to me, lend us five pounds. And he had been paid on the Friday you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 He'd got some good friends helping him to spend it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I've only known father ill once in his life. And that was his last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How long was he ill for before he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Just a matter of a few weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How did that affect the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well there was only me brother and I left then. See we were both working, we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 both in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 the pit so it really didn't affect us much at all then. He was - tell you he was - he was a horse and he got a great big lump grew out here. Eeh what a size it
 got. And - and I said to him, I says, why don't you get to the doctors and get this - see what it is. Look, he says, there's nobody }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 knows}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  how that come, he says, the doctor doesn't know how it's come, he says, and it'll go away the same way as it's come. 
Well he was working just the same and - he went to work one day and they were swinging a plate, you know, on a crane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you get any help from the guardians or the parish or any charities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. Just - as once or twice we got pair of shoes from the police station. Yes. Used t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 o have three holes. Like pricked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 holes, you know, put in them so that you couldn't pawn them. Because people used to get these shoes and pawn them. 'Cos pawn shops were a great thing in them days. Everybody used to go to the p
op shop on a Monday morning, pop things in. Go back when they got paid on Friday, go and get them out, it was - it was part of the tradition of the - this town. Well they - they found that they're popping these school boots as we called them, police stati
on boots. So they started putting three holes in them and the pawn shop wouldn't take 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
When there was somebody in the area who the people disapproved of very strongly, was there any special way that people showed that they didn't like somebody, anyone forced to leave the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I wouldn't say they forced people to leave the district but they were - they were shunned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Just ignored you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you remember any examples?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes there was Maggie Turman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Why was she shunned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 She was a prostitute.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was she the only one in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well as far as we know. There'd be more I dare expect - there would be more. Possible there was a lot of - a lot of men in the district. But she was - she was practically an outcast and she committed suicide in the finish. She gassed herself. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Nobody would speak to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. No, even the men got - that they wouldn't have nothing to do with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was there something bad about her apart from her trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well I don't know, we were - we were young see - at the time we didn't know what these things - were happening for, but in later life as I've looked back I know then, know what was wrong then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were you ever given lessons by one of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Five and a half or six.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 When you first started what time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What time did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Twelve. And went back at half past one to half past three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Right from the beginning did you go morning and afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was it a church school or a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Board school, Beaut it was, it's still there yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What was it called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 ute}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 - board school, Rose Hill, still above the Churchill Street there yet, B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 ute}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was it boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Boys and girls. Mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were you together in the classrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. Mixed. School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh ten minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Tommy - Jackie Levis downstairs. And - we used - come across and - what's the council estate now it used to be the golf course then, we used to nip across the golf course, shorter instead of going round the house, we went over the golf course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Where did you have your midday meal when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Home. Yes, there was no school meals them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - I liked them a little later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 When did you start not to like it then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 When we went to South Shields. After we shifted back to South Shields, I would be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What school were you at at South Shields?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Holy Trinity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 That's a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was that mixed as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. Well there was - there was three sections in the school but the girls was one and the boys another and the infants. But in the B}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 ute}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  the classes was mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What did you feel about the teachers at South Shields then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well I - I don't know why but - why the teacher - Alan Herman. And he was my last teacher in school. And before - before that I had Mr Carter because I would say y
ou were about ten when I went to South Shields and I know me last two teachers was in - in school was Mr Carter and Mr Herman. And - Carter was a - a good sort. Used to be a footballer with Sutherland. Aye. And - oh - everyday you got football. See, well 
t
o us he was a god. Because if we hadn't a ball we used to go and see Mr Carter and he would see you got a ball. And - well I went after that to Mr Herman's class. That was me last year in school, Mr Herman's class. And he was - oh - I daresay a teacher wa
s
 fair enough but he was - to us in them days he was a terror. And - I don't know why but - I never seemed to have a lot of trouble with him. Me - I was always - I was always a good part singer. There were - if the school was singing a melody - melody I wa
s
 always singing a part, I - I would never sing the melody with them, I was singing me own - and - I know one shouldn't boast but I always was, I still am. A good part singer. And - I remember this day, we were going to have a big concert I know and were s
i
nging for whom was going to take the parts. And - there's Mr Carter and Mr Herman, two teachers, and they picked one lad out, he was going to sing one part and then they picked me out, I was going to sing another part. And - you had to come out - when he 
s
houted, you know, and I came out and - what are you laughing at? Well I didn't know that I was laughing. Because life - I've laughed all me life. And - get back to your seat he says. He says, you won't have any part at all in concert. He says, I'll punish
 
you. For no reason at all. See I - I hadn't done anything, not - but that's the way - that's an instance. And another time - we're out in the schoolyard drilling. Doing our drills in the schoolyard you know and it was hips bend and all, well somebody at t
h
at back of me give mea shove. See, naturally, just when you're on your tippy-toes, half fell down and - of course I shoved somebody in front of me. He's seen me. He never anybody else, me. He says, get inside. Get inside. And - of course I had to go insid
e
. And the school drill was all right, they came back in school and he says, come out the front here Madison. He says, undo your trousers and get your trousers down. I said, excuse me sir? He said, you heard what I told you. He said, I'm making an example 
of you. I says, look Mr }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Herman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 , I says, my father}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
s never told me yet to get my trousers down. I says, and don't think you're going to get my trousers down because I'm telling you you're not. He says, do you know who you're speaking to? I says, certainly si
r, I'm speaking to my teacher. I says, and do you know what my teacher's told me? I says, my teachers telling me to do something my own parents don't do. He says, come out here, he says, and I'll take them down. So - I was a big lad when I was at school a
nd I went out the front.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Fourteen. I went out the front. But he was the first on the floor. I had him down as easy - as easy as oh - the lads thought it was great this, yip}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 ee, go on Madison they were shouting. Just them Mr Carter next door he had heard, you know, they only had glass partitions in, he came in and - I told him. Got it down like. And I had to go and see the headmaster, Mr }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Philipson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  and - he says, what happened? And I told him. Of course I know Mr Philipson we
ll, he was also headmaster and choir master too at St Holy Trinity church choir as well and I told him I said, Mr Herman wanted - I says, he was going to take me trousers down when I refused to take 'em down myself. I said, and I told him straight, I said
 
my father didn't do that. And I said he wasn't going to do it. But, he says, you've got to learn discipline. I says, that's not a case of discipline to me. I says, in school, I says, you get a cane, I says, and it's either on your hand or else it's across
 
your bottom but never a bare bottom. I says, that's the difference with me. Well he says, will you take a punishment from me. I said, that all depends what it's going to be sir. I says, the hands. Or - I said, I'll lie across a desk, but not me trousers d
o
wn. Well, he says, I - I'll give you the normal cane on your hands. And - I got I think six off him and - it never worried me. So I - I went back to me class. Herman - out. Out of this school. He says, don't come back here anymore. So I - went out. Next m
o
rning I came back on a Friday morning, I just came and sat at me desk. He said, I thought I told you to leave school? I says, you have no authority to tell me to leave school sir, you're only my teacher. I says, my headmaster hasn't told me to leave schoo
l
. I says, and I don't finish school until tonight. Which I was - was end of me - I was fourteen. I says, I - I finish tonight. I says, I won't be back on Monday. Well, he says, I'm not having you in this class today. Well, I says, that's be up to you and 
t
he headmaster, but I says, my education doesn't finish not unless the headmaster sends me home. Well, he says, I'm not going to have you. I'll give you a job. And he give us all insurance cards for the teachers, every school in South Shields. And I had to
 go round giving the insurance - new insurance cards out. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your teachers emphasise certain things as being very important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Mr Carter especially - character. He says if you have a good character you'll get on anywhere. He says, an
d you'll find that if you lower your character, it's a hard job to get it up again. So, he says, always be careful in what you're doing. Keep out of trouble and keep a good character, that was one thing Mr Carter did impress upon us. And which I think was
 very good advice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Anything else that he thought was important or any of your other teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well - Mr Herman - he was a great churchman and he advocated church. Keep to your church. Which a very few of the lads did, 'cos you know what young lad
s are. I don't say there's anything wrong intentionally but - it's very seldom you get the young lads when leave school like that - attend church regularly. But he did impress upon that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 If you did something the teacher didn't approve of, apart from the example you've just quoted, what generally happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
In school? If - if we done something. You generally got just a cane on the hand. You never got no serious punishment or anything. Well now there was nothing serious during school. We just - we u
sed to get the normal caning. Sometimes it was a cane sometimes a strap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were the girls punished the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well the girls used to say so. The girls used to say they got the cane the same as what we got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What kind of things did you have to do to get the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh - anything. Throwing ink, you know, bits of paper, putting them in inkwell and throwing them about and things like that. Hiding }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 someone\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  books. Hitting someone in a desk and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were your parents interested in what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did they ever ask you what you'd done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your mother or father ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did they meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I don't think they ever did. There was one year I got a prize at school and - nobody there to see you receive it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did the other children in the school come from the same kind of home that you came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 More or less, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did any of the teachers pick out certain children and treat them differently from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Favourites, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What kind of people were picked out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well just the old - ordinary teacher, but of course it was more or less a working class school. There was very few upper class in t
hat school. See the - as we call the upper class, they used to go to Richards and Days in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
. That was like the secondary school. Yes. See the - if you're anybody at all you went to Richards and Days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 In your school can you tell me something about the kind of people who were picked to by the teachers as favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh - just ordinary pets. The ones that used to tell tales, they were the pets. If anybody went to the teacher and told a tale and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 They were the favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What kind of gangs did you have in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Just the same as any other school. All - more lads of one age kept together though. See, if - if lads of thirteen - twelve and thirteen, they kept together. Then there's the nines and tens, they were b
elow you. And you looked up to them; when you got in your final year, oh you were the big boys. You ruled the school, big boys and play and anything, if we wanted part of the yard when were big boys, we took it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So it was just age gangs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, that's what they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 There weren't any smaller groups than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, no. No, groups wasn't known in them days, it was just the gangs in the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you notice in the school any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I wouldn't
 say they were left out. We had one or two who - backward children in the school. Weren't - well I would call - mentally retarded. That's - you know, now, speaking now. But you can understand now why they weren't - the same as what we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 But of the people who you would think of as normal were there any that struck you as being very lonely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, wouldn't say we had any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you go on to another school after this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 From }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8330246\charrsid8601884 Wallsend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 . No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 From your last school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 South Shields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 When you were fourteen you left there didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I - I left there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you go to any other school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, no, I finished then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You were then how old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Fourteen. I started work straight away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 If you'd had the chance would you have stayed longer at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Have you any regrets about your education generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I didn't take advantage of the chances I had. Now, looking back. I know now that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What would you have liked to have done then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - more study. And I would have liked to have had more study.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 But do you think you benefited from going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I certainly benefited. Yes. But had I had extra education I think I could have benefited more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 While you were at school did you have a part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Or any means of getting a little bit of extra money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Pit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How did you get the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well I just went along and asked if they wanted any lads. St Hilda colliery, South Shields. I just went and asked them if they had any lads and - they asked us how old I was I think and I says, ask us what me religion was.
 And I told 'em I was Church of England. And they give me a job, start on Monday. I start on the screens. Seven and sixpence a week. That's what I had, seven and sixpence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well when the coal comes out the pit - you know, it comes up the shaft and it's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 tipped}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  out of the tubs onto these }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 screens}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Is that like a big conveyor belt?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. And you've got to pick all the rubbish out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How can you tell what's rubbish and what's not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 that\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  
just left to you, you get no training anything, you can toss anything. You see. Which you used to do until you - you learnt see because - what we called the boss was the kicker, we called him the kicker. He would stand watching you. And if you were standi
ng not throwing anything out - oh, he was - on me straight away. So you used to toss anything out, it doesn't matter what it was, you toss something out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 On early turn I worked from seven o'clock to two. And then on the back shift worked from two 'til ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You never worked at night then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh we didn't work Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 On a Saturday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So you worked five and a half days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Five and a half days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you get any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh no, holidays with pay? By God.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And you were paid seven and six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Seven and sixpence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you think that was a fair wage at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh well, it was as much as you could get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You thought it was good enough did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Yes. I thought if I - if I went to shipyard I wouldn't get as much as that as apprenticeship. I wouldn't get as much as that, I thought I was getting big money by going to pit. That's one of the things that attracted me to the pit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So you were quite happy with it really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, I - I was quite happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you give any of it to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I used to give her it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you know what it was spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well household, I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 It went in with the other money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 It went just with the housekeeping money. I used to get a shilling back pocket money. I used to get a shilling pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So you were much richer than you were before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How did you get on with the other people that you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh, house afire. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What kind were they who worked on the screen, were they lads of your own age mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 All young lads. You went on the screen before you went down the pit. That was your first job as you started at the pit, on the screens.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 He was good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What did you feel about him, did you like him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 He - he was a terror, and - used to curse and swear he - by God. And he's broad Scotch
 you know. If the kicker sent you to his office - oh you didn't half get a dressing down. And I can remember going and asking him - I was going to be confirmed and I went and asked him could I be off this night. And I was having to be con - I was going to
 be confirmed at St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Hilda\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 of South Shields. And - I can remember - when I went in office he said, you're going to be what? Going to be confirmed. - what the hell's that? Well I says, in church, I says - you're confirmed, a said, you're - you're taking par
t in the church life practically. He says, you - he says, you didn't tell me you were going into church. But - it just showed his - at the bottom there was a man in him. He let us go all right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What did you feel about the work you were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well I didn't like it when I first went. But I gradually - I was only there six weeks, then I went down the pit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 By the end of six weeks you got promoted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes, I - 'cos I was getting more used to it and everything. The - you were only there so
 you - you learn all these little knick-knacks and things. And it was getting - grand I thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you tell me about the different jobs you did in the pit from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 starting}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  on the screens up until 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - I started on the screens first, I was
 - the screeners you called them. Then I - I went down the pits, I was on the screens I think it was six weeks, then I went down the pit. The first job was trapper boy. And all you sit and do, you open the canvas door when the pitter used to come through 
w
ith their pony. And - - the built these canvas doors every so often to regulate the flow of air. See, it's hard to explain, but all - down the pit is regulated down the pit by canvas - see, there's half the roadway is canvassed off and the air goes down o
n
e way and comes back out of another. Of course the air must be kept moving in a pit. Well, the only way they can stop it from going where it shouldn't go is by building these doors. And - of course they keep opening and shutting, well your first job is to
 go down as a trapper boy and just sit and open these doors. You put a rope on and - just - instead of you getting up to open the door you just sit and pull the - then from there you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How long did you do that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh was only a matter of week - week and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Six weeks on the screens and then a week and a half on the traps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Yes. Then I went into the - into the production centres as you call it. And - I went as lantern boy first. Landing boy. See the driver used to fetch all the tubs 
from the coalface out to the landings and he used to make them up into sets. Well our job was to couple them all up. You put the little chains on, coupling chains as we called them. And used to put twenty-four in a set, that made a set up. Then you put a 
r
ope on one end and a rope on the other, main and tail as you call it. See, one pulls and the other one holds back, it seems Irish, 'cos - but - that's the idea. See one pulls and the other one draws you down the hill, a main and tail. And of course they g
o out of the shaft bottom. Then from there I went driving.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How long were you doing that on the landing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh - three month I think, three or four months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So that take you to about five months since you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Then I got onto driving then you - you're a big lad then, you got a pony then. And then from driving I went onto putting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How long were you driving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I think about - twelve month. From - first going on the pit and I got putting. And I went as a putter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What's a putter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well that's taking the tubs from the driver to the man in - the actual man that's hewing the coal. Yes. 'Cos with the - there's nothing like that nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You worked as a putter for how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I think it was two year. And then the coal cutting machine started to come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 This must have been just before the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
The '18 war. Yes. And the coal cutting machines was coming in. Compressed air they were. There was not such a thing as electric in them days in the pit. The
 coal cutting machines - they were terrible noisy thing. But oh my - well they used to get the coal out all right. And - I fancied - coal cutting. So I - I put an application in like I - I would like to be a cutter. And - all right. But if I - if I went c
utting it meant I had to give up all claim to be a - a hewer. See, they're - they were - in the pit, they're clannish about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You could either be one or the other but not both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. See - when you're a hewer, you're the top. You couldn't get 
no farther. Only thing you - if you - hewer if you wanted farther you had to go and be an official, that was like a deputy or an overlooker. When you're a hewer at top of the class. Well when you're a cutter you're on top of the class and all. And - I fan
cied the cutting. And - I had to go and learn it like.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 At another pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
No, at the same pit. But you went with the people that was installing the cutting machines, the makers. They - they sent a team of men up just to train - the employees at the
 colliery. And - I went and - it suited me. Oh God I was - I know it seems sound boasting but - it was bairns play to me. Even - even the - the men that was from the works, they couldn't understand how I could handle the machine as I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So you were really successful?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
It - it wasn't only that, it was me build. See, I - I was - you see, small and squat. Where majority of men was - eeh, ten inches, a foot taller than me, well it was making it terrible awkward for them. Well I could get down, I cou
ld handle the machine where they were having trouble with it. And - and I went on famously.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
How did your hours of work vary from the beginnings when you were just doing a five and a half day week, and you were working from seven 'til two did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Seven 'til two, then two 'til ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did that change very much during the first four or five years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes, when you went down the pit you were on three shifts. Eeh - you - you worked over night as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you work any longer though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, no, your shift was the same. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You still never worked Sunday or Saturday afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Sometimes - after I got cutting I was working Saturdays and Sundays. See, as the machine became more popular - you were working. Because they found 
that - it was more beneficial to have the machines working over the weekend, you could have all your coal cut, it was fired already for the coal you was coming in on the Monday. It was a big benefit to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you get any holidays with pay by now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How did your wage increase in the first four or five years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Seven and six a week when I first went on the pit was eight and six, got a shilling a week rise when we went down the pit. And then it gradually came up, when I was putting I w
as getting about three pound ten - four pound which was supposed to be a good wage then. Well that - that was piece work. You - you - you were piece worker then. But - after I got onto the machines and I got properly in the way I was making seven, eight p
ound a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 That was back in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 That was good money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
And after that I was making more after that. Because - they started complaining, the colliery started complaining that the machines was getting too far ahead of the men. Se
e, which was only natural. So - I - there was the hue and cry, some of the men, the old fashioned hewers you know, stop the machines altogether. Not safe and - and the noise they make, 'cos the din off them was terrible, especially down the pit. And - som
e
 would have them scrapped. Well - I was one of the - the head cutters at the time and I was just a boy mind. And - I got union meeting one days and I says, well, I says - there's a lot of talk here, I says, about scrapping the machines and this and that, 
I says, why can't we work together? I says, why can't we work together? I says, there's nothing to stop us, and which would be beneficial to everybody. I says, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 company'll}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  get more coal and we'll get better wages. Well - how to work together? Well, I say
s, one hewer and one coal cutter to work together as a team. That's six on one team, that's three shifts. One cutter and one hewer in each of the three shifts. I says, the coal cutter that cut half his face - what we used to call - what you are cutting. S
e
e it all depends on what was above you, the land above you, an area as a collier could work, because you had to leave so much coal in the pit. I'm not going to say it was always left mind. But - there was so much of the coal left so as to support the grou
n
d. Well, I says, if we start this new scheme, I says, the coal cutter can cut half his face, I said, draw it and fire it, I says, and the hewers fill that away, I say, you haven't got to hew at all, just fill that straight away. Cutters cutting at other s
ide, time of that, M said, means that there's never any waiting of coal at all, you've got coal all the time. And they thought it was worth a try like. And by God, what a trial. We doubled our wages and I was getting fourteen pounds a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And this was still in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Yes. And - and they got up - and some of them got up and they turned round and - I wasn't eighteen at the time - they got up and said I should be taken off the machines 'cos I wasn't old enough. And they took us off the machine, but mind not for long.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You didn't give your money to your mother because she was dead?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I gave it me grandmother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 When you were earning seven pounds a week and fourteen pounds a week what did you do with all that money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Give it to me grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 All of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Every bit of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How much did you get back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Some weeks I got two shillings, some weeks I got three shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 That's all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Even when you were bringing home fourteen pounds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I went right up
 'til 1926 and it came to 1926 strike and just before that 1926 strike twenty pounds a week was nothing. When I was working in them days. And I - I was giving me grandmother everything mind. And - if - if I was in me family me brother would tell you, that
 many a time I asked her for tuppence to get me pit bottom soldered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 That wouldn't happen these days would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you continue to get on well with the people you were working with, apart from the old chaps who wanted you taken off the machine?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes. I got on all right with them outside the pit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about the boss, when you started earning this very big money was he pleased with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh - oh by heavens, it's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You liked the job more and more I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh
 definitely because everything was progressing. The - the scheme went right through the colliery. In fact it went other collieries after that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You made a name for yourself then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, it went to other collieries after that. In - in 1926 I was thinking about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You were on these cutting machines right up 'til '26?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Yes. Right up t- the - '26. And - I was - knocking about with me first wife like and I wanted to get married. So - few weeks before the strike, I can remember, I went home and 
I never said anything to me grandmother, I give her six pounds. I put six pounds notes on the table. I says, there grandma, I says, I - I'm - I'm going to give you that every week now 'cos, I says, I want to save up to get married. She says, how do you th
i
nk I'm going to keep you on that? She says, you know the money I've been getting off you. I says, I know, I says, but I want to save up to get married. She says, I canna keep you on that, she said, you might as well get yourself out. So I says, right. And
 I just picked the six pound up. Eventually I had to get out. I had been giving her all that money all them years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Six pound a week was a good wage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I think it was. By heavens. You can get lodgings now for six pounds a week. But - me father was g
etting the biggest part of that. That six pound. See - while I was paying the house, he - he wasn't tipping his share up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 After the strike did you go back to cutting again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Never went back to pit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 That's when you went to bus driving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. I went to Canada. I went to Canada.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What did you do in Canada?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
I went to Courtaulds experimental factory. The first experimental factory they had. It was - it was a marvellous experience. Used to throw pulp in one end of the machine and it came out artificial silk at the other. It was marvellous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What was your job there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
I was what you call the doffer. You - you had to wear rubber clothes. And - it was all acid, everything was acid. All the works was glass and everything see to res
ist acid. And God, burn, oh. Yet everybody - we were - but I was terrible, I don't know whether it'd be me skin or not, I had awful hands. Got awful and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was that good money?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 That was good money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Two year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What made you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well - after the '21 strike, well before the strike was settled I got this chance of a job in Canada. I'd no more thoughts of going to Canada that what you had. Me first wife, she was a great spiritualist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You were saying your first wife's mother was a great ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Spiritualist. And - I was out of work see with the strike and - they had this sale of work one day. And went - 'course we went to the sale of work and - there was a Mrs Crisp, a clairvoyant. Her husban
d was a sea captain - they were well-to-do people - and she used to tell fortunes sixpence a time you know. And they wanted me to - go and have me fortune told. So I said, yes, I might as well give her sixpence as well as anybody else. And - I went into t
h
is room where Mrs Crisp was. She says, you've just come in here for a joke haven't you? I said, well, I'll be quite honest, I have. Well she says, I want you to listen, take note of what I'm going to tell you. She says, have you got anything belonging to 
s
omeone who's passed on, connected with you? Oh - yes, I said, I've got me grandfather's watch. Pocket watch. She said will you give it to me a minute? And I give her this pocket watch and God you'd just think me grandfather was sitting talking to us. Her 
voice changed, she talked exactly like him. And she didn't know me grandfather, she didn't know me even. And she talked - '}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 cos}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 he was a proper Cockney - and she talked exactly like him. Well she says, I know you just came in here for a joke but I want you t
o take particular notice if what I'm going to tell you. She says, you're going overseas. And she says I cannot - I cannot get where it is. It's either Canada or Australia. She says, I can tell you that, it's either Canada - she says, I cannot get it clear
.
 Don't go to Canada, Australia yes. Well I had no intentions - of going to anywhere. As far as I was concerned I was going back to pit. Well, she says, you're going and she says, you - you're going to be married very very quickly. Well, I wasn't even - we
l
l I say I wasn't thinking about - we had talked about getting married but - not as things were because we were on strike at the time. Well, she says, you're going to be married very quickly. And - various things passed off. But she says - you're going awa
y but if you go to Canada, she says, you'll come back. She says, my advice, if you get the offer of Australia go to Australia. Well I - had no - getting an offer from anywhere. At any rate, within a week I got a letter offering us a job in Canada.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Had you written for it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
No. But this lad that I knew, he wrote to us and Bill Martin he had gone out to Canada, he was a shipyard worker and he had gone out to Canada and he had done well. And he wrote and knew that I was on strike like you know, he wro
te, come out, there's a job for us. So - I says, Norah, what about it? Well, she says, it's up to you. I says, and will you go. I said, mind, means leaving home. Oh she says, I don't mind. So I made enquiries and that and we found it would make it much ea
sier if we were married for Norah coming out. So we decided to get married there and then. We got a special }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 license}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
, cost twenty-four pound, we were married in three days. It was the talk of the town. And I went out to Canada and - arrived on the Saturday - on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Saturday}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
. In Quebec, we arrived in Quebec in the seven day because it was boats then there was no planes then in them days. And - I made me way up to corner of - that's where I went to - a place called Cornwall - on the Sunday. See we stopped on the sh
ip overnight and we left on the Sunday morning. I got into }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Cornwall}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 Sunday night. And - this lad was at the station to meet us coming. He says, now - he says, I'm supposed to be at work now. He says, the boss is letting us come down to meet you. He says - do you want to start work in the morning? Oh, I said, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 let\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 have a look at the place first. I says, here, I says, look at the place. Well, he said, you can start in the morning any time you like. I says, look, I says, you'd better get back to work. You've 
got to go back to work. I says, take me to me digs, I says, and I'll see you in the morning and we'll talk things over in the morning. I see him on the Monday morning like and - we were walking down the main street, Pitt Street they called it. And - you'd
 
better - I hears a big fire - you talk about the western, there was a big fellow, shot. He had robbed a bank in Toronto. And the police was waiting on him coming through in the car. And he was shot right in the street. That the first day in Canada. But an
y
 rate I - I gets a job and - had a Yorkshire boss. Alf Shorts they called him. And I never in my life hard a man curse like him. I've heard some men swear but never - beat this fellow. And he wasn't talking to a soul you know. The mill was a great long - 
o
h as long as this street and the machines was all set down all side, a gangway down each end. And he used to come in and walk down the mill. Curse and swear, you've never heard anything like it. And he - he wasn't talking to a soul. Not - not directly. No
, he used to tell 'em straight, he said, if I come round and - oh yes, yes, next thing I turn round he said, you're away smoking or something. He says, but if I come through like that he says, keeps everybody on their toes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you enjoy your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 couple}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  of years in Canada?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
I - I went on and - tell you I got me hands very bad. And I had a chargehand sat at the same desk as me in Trinity school. Jack Roland, aye. But we never hit it. I don't know why. I - I - I don't know yet why - 'cos I never done any
thing to him. But he - he - I don't know why, I've never done anything to him, I used to do me work but me hand was getting bad. Well it was that bad that I was medical attention twenty-four hours a day. Yes, it was that bad. And - me hands }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 got}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  bad, I went
 to see the nurse and she said I had to have light work. I had to get off the acid. So I went to working at night, 'cos it was twenty-four hours. There was no break at all. If a machine stopped an hour the whole process was ruined because - the friscus, t
h
at's what they called the stuff that the pulp used to make to make the - silk, used to turn to jelly. It was ruined, hat do be - moving always twenty-four hours a day. Seven days a week, it never stopped see, it had to keep this continuous flow. And - I t
o
ld her I had to have a light job. Oh - no job there, that's your job on machine there. Well, I says, I'll have to go home, I says, and go compensation that's all. Well in Canada compensations a vastly different thing to - to in England. See well the gover
n
ment pays the compensation there, not the firm. But the firm's got to pay the government and they don't like you on compensation at all. See they'll do - they'll get you anything but bar compensation. But any rate I was getting ready to go and - who shoul
d
 come up but the head man, Mr Shorts. What's wrong Jock? Oh, I says, I'm going home, I says, I've had me fingers done, I says, and I've been told I've got to have light work. I says, and Rowden told us I've got to get out the machine. He says, what light 
-
 what light work is there here? Well, I says, I'm not saying light work, I says, but there's plenty of jobs to get us away from acid, 'til me hands get a chance to heal. He says, get your coat off. Oh, I says, I'm not going back on that machine. I says, I
 
cannot. He says, get your ruddy coat off, he says, or you'll not get another chance. Get it off. So I thought then, well - the least I can - see what he's going to offer us. So I takes me coat off and he takes us upstairs. He says, come with me. And from 
-
 the machines downstairs all the silk used to go upstairs to be steamed, because all the acid and everything had to be taken out of it, see, before the girls could - manhandle it. And there was nothing to do - it was all - all you do was put the stuff in 
the cabinets and the machines - they had to be at like thermostat and that and everything you know, had to be kept at a certain temperature and the steam, humidity and everything. Well it was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 collar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  and tie job. Nearly double the money. It was a plum. And
 you also had charge of two thousand French girls, French Canadians. On - on that floor. Eeh you were responsible to two thousand girls. So he took us in, he says, now here you are, he says, there's a job there for you. He said, you've got a good job here
.
 He says, look after it. He says, if any of these buggers in here gets after you, have nothing to do with them. That was the women. And he had a woman living with him. So - I says, oh, I says, you needn't worry about that. I says, I've got a wife coming o
n
 shortly. He says, look, you're the same as me, he says, you've got a cock and if you've got the chance to use it you'll throw it out the way, that's the type of man he was, see. So I gets this job and - furiously - oh me health and everything, me wife ca
m
e out and had a lovely home. Oh doing fine then. And - goes in one morning and Mr Wainwright, he says, have you heard the news Madison? I says, no, I says. He says, have you heard about Mr Shorts? No, I says, what's wrong with him? Oh, he says, he collaps
e
d through the night and he's in hospital. He says, he collapsed, he says, we don't know what's wrong, anything but, he says, he collapsed in the night and he's been taken to hospital. Oh, I says, that's - pity to hear that, bad news. Because he was - he w
a
s a football friend as well. And we had a good team. I - I sent to Newcastle for strips. Aye. Black and white Newcastle strip. He was that keen to have a good team. He says, if you know any footballers in England wants a job - he says, if you know anybody
 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 who}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 can play football send for them, bring them over, he said, I'll give them a good job. He was - I can remember we were playing in the final this night, the final in the cup and always played left half and - this night - Bobby Thomas, he was inside left,
 couldn't play. So - he says to me he says, well he says, only one thing he says, you'll go up there, he says, we'll fetch Jock Green in, a little Scotch lad, he wasn't as tall as me. He says, I'll fetch him in. In your place. Well, I says, I - I says, I'
d
 sooner stop in me own place for - for a final tie you know, put in another place. And we - it was played in the first ground, lovely ground. The - underneath the turf was tiles. The - the whole field was tiled underneath the turf was laid - oh magnificen
t field. And we had the whole town out. It was a great night. God, I missed a sitter. Inside left. He runs down the touchline and the wife all sitting, you bastard, burn your bloody boots. Eeh what a man.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you win that match?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 We were getting 
beat 2-0 at half time. And I'd missed two sitters. Two that anybody could have scored but - I wasn't comfortable man. If I'd been in me own place, half back, I - I'd have been all right. And I asked him, I says, now it's half time - raised the dressing ro
o
m man. He says, you bugger, there's them going to walk away with this cup again. I says, they's 'll not walk away with the cup, I says, we'll still get it man. I says, but let me go back in me own place, I says, and let Jock - Jock Green go up in the forw
a
rd line. But I had - had no shields for the ante - play around centre forward. And we had a good - anyway we went on for second half and we start off well and I puts a ball though to Bert, I says, go on Bert. I say, I shove it through for you. And Bert aw
ay and I say, I'll follow you up man. Went away and Bert }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 gets}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 a good - he should have scored easy. But he shoved it across to me. Well I - it was a case of just tapping it in. 2-1, oh it wasn't so bad. That's another, I goes in, scores again. That was twice
. We're drawing. Up again, the scores 3-2. Well we eventually wins the match, 4-8.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And was he excited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh - he - he - he was old 'un but he - he - if he could he would have given all Canada that night. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 But then he collapsed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Aye,
 well, I tell you, they took him to hospital and he collapsed very shortly after the math and about eleven o'clock in the morning worked came in, he was dead. He had died. Well, the mill went on just the same and I went to work the next day like and the f
irst thing - the old schoolmate, the chargehand, see he automatically stopped up to his job. He come up and, you, downstairs. Straight away. First thing he ever does, the first job he ever done. Come and put me back on the machines. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did that decide you to come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
So went on like this and I gradually got - into a state again. Then I can remember going in this morning to have me fingers done and the doctor was there, he done it and I can remember him doing the right hand and I passed out. I
 was in such a state I passed out. Any rate the - they gets us home and about a fortnight mind and doctor says, you're finished at the machines, you're not going back on them machines any more. He says, you're one of these persons he says, that your skin'
s
 not standing up to this at all. He says, you've got to have another job. So I went to work at nighttime, I told Rowden, I says - has there been any word from the doctor? No, he says, what's the doctor got to do with it? Well, I said, the doctor's told me
 
that I have not got to go back on the machines any more. He says, have you ever been out of work in Canada in the winter? I says, no. I says, have you? Aye, he says, I've had a winter, he says, and mind it's bad. Well, I says, don't worry yourself Jack, I
 said, if you can take one winter, I said, I can do two any time. I says, can you remember the day I dragged }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13321278\charrsid8601884 you down Trinity school like - Tr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 inity school yard and beat the life out of you? Oh, he says, that's a long time since. Aye, I said, and I'm twice t
he man I am now to what I was then. Oh, he says, don't throw your weight about here, and try to show me up like. And I - I lost me head. And I just got stuck into him. And I did. I picked him up and I clapped him down, oh but I did. Well where I got the s
t
rength from I don't know but - I was past myself to tell you honest truth. But anyway I give him a damn good hiding, and all the Frenchmen was up they thought it was wonderful, the mill was in uproar over it. So - I knew that was me finished. I just come 
o
ut of the mill and then I come home. The wife said, what's the matter with you? Oh, I says, I'm finished. I said I've had a row with Rowden there, I says, he might take us to court yet. I said, because I - I gave him a damn good hiding there. And in the m
eantime, her - her mother at home knew how bad I'd been like and she says there was a business for sale. A food business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So you had this fight with Rowden and then you heard with your mother-in-law?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Aye, so - we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 decided}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  there, I said, oh we'll go home and buy this business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What were you then, about twenty-eight or twenty-nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Twenty-nine. I says, we'll go home and buy this business. So - went down to shipping office. I want to book to singles back to England. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Oh you'll want returns, you're sure to come back. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
I said, I want to singles, I said. I went and got two singles back home, I went up to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Percy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 Fulthrop, he was the - the big store there and 'cos I had a lovely television - wireless, there was no television them days. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Big ten valve
, Mohawk they called it I can remember, lovely thing and a speaker up in the corner of the wall you know, lovely machine it was but I only had it on the H.P., see I couldn't afford it because we were only just setting up home and I went and told Percy Ful
throp like, I says, I've come to see what you'll give us for that set, I says, I know I haven't paid a great lot off it, I says, but we're going back home. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And - was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 all right}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 , well, he says, I'll tell you what, he said, I'll give you what you've paid. And 
he give us - and he give us everything back what I'd paid. And I went to draw money out the bank to come home and - the bank manager says, leave something in, he says, because you'll come back again you know. Oh, I says, I'm not leaving anything, I says, 
I'll never come back here. He says leave something in. I left half a dollar in. I've still got half a dollar in the bank there.
