\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So what happened when you came back to England, did you get this business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 We came home - arrived at Newcastle statio
n on Sunday night. And we came across the bridge at the Central station and walked out to the gate there in Central Station and there was a chap walked up and he went to the wife, he says, excuse me, he says, are you Norah Mendel? That was my }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 wife's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  maiden
 name see. I says, no, I says, she's not. He said, I thought it couldn't be he said, because Norah Mendel's in Canada. And - I never let on see and I was nudging Norah not to say anything so I said, you don't know me? No, he says, I can't say that I do. W
e
ll, I says, you should do. I said, you're Mr Melville aren't you? He says, aye, he says, I'm Mr Melville. Well, he says, I says, this is Norah Mendel, she's Norah Madison now. Well Good God, he says, you're in Canada man. I said, we were 'til a week ago. 
B
ecause they never knew we were coming home. It was that sudden, we came home, there wasn't a soul in the house. I said, I know where we'll find your mother. Going up the spooky meetings as we calls it, spiritualist meetings you know. Sure enough her mothe
r was at a spiritualist meeting. We came over like that. And the business was bankrupt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So it was no good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So I was on - I couldn't go on the dole.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So what was your first job then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - only from 1914 up to '26, see, the time I was i
n the pit I'd done all kinds. See because the pit work was only eight hours a day then, only eight hours over, it was finished I was - I learnt to drive motor cars, I worked on the river, helped the shipping chandlers on the rivers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 These were all jobs you got paid for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh aye. These are all spare time - time I was in the pit. This was all the time I was at the pit. I - I learnt all this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How many spare time jobs did you have then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I worked for Mickey Hanlan, shipping butcher - shipping - shipping butcher you know, there's - you - have a launch }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 and on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 the river, go about supplying ships. I worked for him. I worked for John Gilroy the food merchants. That's where I learnt to drive. And I was doing spare time work at Cavan Carriage Company, funeral work. All that time at the pit you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So you were working a fifteen hour day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh - twenty-four hours a day many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Just those three jobs or did you have any more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh well there were various little ones. Discharging ships, humping taties, now when the tatie ships come in discharge }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 potatoes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  carry them into the warehouse store and that. I - I anything there's any money to be had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So it wasn't just twenty pounds a week was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. By heavens it wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What was your first full time job after you came back from Canada?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 On United.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were you driving from the start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. Started as a driver.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And you continued right up to .....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 194 - 1965.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Without any break?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, 1960, I'm
 telling a lie, I left in 19 - I started in '29 on United and I left in 1960. I was driving all that time. But I - I was a rebel really.
