they did their own servicing. See if a machine went wrong it was packed up and sent away to Bells. Well - what the company was going to do, they were going to change over to these Setrights, that's what they have now. These are very complicated machines, 
t
hey print everything inside. That's four hundred - four hundred and sixty odd moving parts in the machine. It's only about that size. It's a marvellous thing. Well, applied for mechanic to service these. And I put in an application. I thought well, it - i
t
's a home job, you see, it's off driving. And - I didn't think I would get it mind because it was for all the area, it wasn't just Newcastle, it was all the area. And I got a letter, had to go for an interview. And I was selected for the job. And - had to
 go down to London for two weeks to where they made the machines. The Setright factory and you got a proper course there, to service the machine. Which was very interesting.
