u had your column and you had your cylinder and it was all worked on a coil root so you could work right round the face. And it was all - tricky work setting because you had to study your gradient which way your coal was lie, see because you - your machin
e only cut dead level. So if you set your machine level and your coal was rising you're going to be into the stone. Well you had to know the contour of your coal and everything.
