\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Every week. And
 I used to - I used to play well with them men, you weren't fair and yet nobody wants to go and shout for them. They all they wanted was somebody else to do their shouting for them. - They'd pay their subscriptions and everything but you could never get t
hem to the meeting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you do some of the shouting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What kind of things did you do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well we had deputations to the manager.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You went on these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How about the strikes, the general strikes and any other strikes before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well we had little bits of strikes but the big strike was 1926, the general strike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What part did you play in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well I - I was out of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 As far as the union was concerned, starting it off? Did you play any part in any meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Oh yes. We had - were meeting and everything and it was decided to have - food kitchens. See in the - in the union halls we made soup and things for the miners, their families would come and get. And then they got - we couldn't get
 supplies on account of the general strike see everybody was on strike. And - our lads was - had spent a lot of time motor driving, see the time I was in the pit, I told you before, we had two or three jobs, I was on the river, I was all over the time I w
a
s at the pit. I was never still. And I'd done a lot of work for Gilroy the fruit merchant of South Shields and - I went and seen old John and he says, if you'll drive the lorry, he says, you can have as many potatoes, vegetables as you can take. So I volu
n
teered to drive the lorry. And I went with a police escort. I had barbed round the windscreen you know and on the sides and I drove the lorry to the miner's balls delivering potatoes and vegetables and things. Then - I was a striker and yet I was breaking
 the strike at the same time. It was a funny position to be in. But yet, we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 on strike and yet we had to live. And it meant that the women }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 children was the biggest sufferers. Well, I thought it was only thing can do, try and get through. I went thro
ugh barriers and road blocks, all things with the wagon. I - what I - I had an awful name. But yet, it was for their own good. I was a trade unionist and yet I was breaking the union action at the time but I didn't mind, I thought it was for their good.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What would you have thought if some truck drivers had come working down the mines getting coal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well if they could have done it and they could have getting in. But I'd bet members of the union first. You could spend they wouldn't get into the union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you think generally that bosses and workers had the same interests in the period round about 1918?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were they working for the same things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How were they different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh well, as - as far as the empl
oyers - you were muck. All they want was the best they could get out of you. They had no concern of your welfare or anything. See, the - if you're off work sick you're off work sick and nobody ever }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 bothered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  you or - there was no Lloyd George or anything li
ke that in them days. And - the boss just hadn't - if he passed you in the street, you - you'd to hardly speak to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What kind of things were the bosses looking for that the workers wouldn't aim for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well the - the only thing a boss was concerned about is how much he was going to get out of you for his days work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What were you concerned about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
As much as we could get wages because the wages were so low in them days. Taking for my self mind - my wages wasn't low. Because I was one of
 the lucky lads. I learnt the machines and it was just - seemed as thought it was a natural thing, I took it like a duck to water. And I was making money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You were nearly a millionaire before you were twenty weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you think t
hat there were divisions of interest amongst workers? Between rained craftsmen and other workers for example, were there different things they were interested in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I wouldn't say they were interested - the workers and the bosses - they all had the same interests outside of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
I mean things they wanted, were there any differences between different kinds of workers, between skilled workers and unskilled workers in what they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13321278\charrsid8601884 trying}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  to get from work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh well - the skilled worker, he 
done his craft and that was all he done. But an unskilled man, he had to do anything. Your overman or your boss would just come in and - he might send you on go and draw pipes up and all work and that, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 timber}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  from on old working. He might send you on leadi
ng water away, anything. An unskilled man. But the craftsman, as we call a craftsman, such as the cutter and the hewer, they never done anything else. Not unless there was an emergency mind. If there was emergency then you - you all mucked in and done wha
t was - and there was often emergencies in them days. Because the bosses used to steal coal - oh Yes, they had no respect for men's lives or anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You were saying they used to steal coal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. We used to work what was called burn pillar. Tha
t was usually - what we call a board, maybe you're driving a board ten feet wide - ten yards wide rather and that was - the management supposed to be. That was on account of compensation of ground above, see, for the land that was above. It can only take 
s
o much coal out so it stops subsidence. But you could always gamble that you're driving the board twice the width that you're supposed to be. That was stolen coal. When the plans, if any of these old workings went - if there was a case such as compensatio
n
 the coal; board turn round and say, well, the bore was only driven ten yards wide but that bore you could say it was entirely up to twenty yards wide. And they used to do things like that. Well all that meant that was endangering men's lives. Because you
 were taking too much coal out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Do you think that when you started full time work this changed your general attitude to life, did it open your eyes to things that you didn't know about before, make you think in a different way about anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh definitely. After - after I got into the pit and see actual life and the conditions of life it changed the outlook altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you say in any particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - you seen how the man was being exploited. See the - they didn't care a damn 
what you were. All they wanted was their pound of flesh. And if you were prepared to give a pound of flesh you were out, they had no use for you at all. It was no good going saying oh you were sick. It was get in there and get the days work. Hard. People 
-
 this generation - I know it seems awful to talk about this but this generation doesn't know - it's only twenty-five, forty years ago what the conditions of life were then. They can't realize, the young people today, they can't realize what - we went thro
ugh in them days. I know I - you think you're boasting and that but it's facts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You were living with your granny after you left school weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you continue living at home from the time you started work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, I never went into lodgings once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Right up 'til you got married when you were twenty-six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Right until twenty-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did this change your relationship with your father in any way when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I - me father was still the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And you behaved the same way to him did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Yes. I still though he was a good father for all he was still drinking as much. Me mother was dead and - me father was still drinking as much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about your relationship with your brother after you started work was that the same or did that change?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No - that was just the same. And when me brother was old enough I got him into the pit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 There was only the one brother living then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. There was only the one brother living then. All the other four was dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you spend Sundays any differently after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. Went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Even when you were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. Yes, I was confirmed after I started work. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 
I was confirmed after - I was on the pit, working - I was on the screens mine, I wasn't down the pit when I was confirmed but we still went to our church and that and the choir and the scouts. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, working didn't change - it didn't change the life that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you take any interest in politics after you'd started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
No, not for a long time. I would be - oh getting into thirties before I started really - deal, you know, act - I take active part in politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What were your views, your political views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well I - I'm staunch Labour man. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well because what I had seen of life I found that the - the Liberals and the Conservatives are called - weren't for the working class. And there's only one party which could represent the working class as I though
t in them days. And that was the Labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You wouldn't have voted before 1919 would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I wasn't twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you feel under any pressure from anybody, like your bosses at work, to vote for any particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I wou
ldn't say - we actually didn't have much to do with our bosses because you bosses was another class. See, they didn't mix much with you. Not 'til later on years mind when you got into the 1930's, then you were getting the bosses coming into the clubs and 
things, come and have a drink at night and that and all - and you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 gradually}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 were getting more and more together. But mind that wasn't the owners as you call the bosses, I'm talking about the - your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 charge hands}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  and your bosses, your overmen and like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you belong to a political party, were you a member of the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I wasn't an actual member but - I used to work in the headquarters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You used to work at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. Old Walerow, that was the first man we ever worked for. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you take part in any political activity other than election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, just go meetings. You know, to what the - not Labour party meetings, were union meetings. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 But you didn't go to any Labour party meetings apart from election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Just election times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Did you carry on spending your spare time in the same way after you started work, you said earlier you used to spend your weekends and evenings playing about, playing football especially and going down to that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 den}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Burnt Close.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you carry on doing the same sort of things or did your life change in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh, me life changed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Because - oh I'd gone back to South Shields as I got older. See - after me mother died we went
 back to South Shields. And of course all me background then was all on the river. Because we lived at Mill Down, that was a notorious place in those days. It was a seamen's preservation, all the foreign seamen used to - designed on ships and discharged s
h
ips and that you know. There used to be these ships runners - it was very interesting and I was - all me life. Before I was in the pit - there used to be a - a policeman used to pass our door, a river policeman, old Jack Plum and he used to tell me grandm
other. He'd say, we'll pick that boy out of the river yet. That was me. Couldn't keep us off the river - in me spare time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 That was after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes. Talk about lads now being bad, I'll give you one instance. I'll be - eighteen at t
he time - eighteen or nineteen at the time and it was on a Bank Holiday Monday and I says to the lads and lasses as we used to go to Crown Dance Hall at South Shields every Saturday night, I says, come down to Mill Dam on Monday morning and I'll take you 
a
ll to Wryton. I went and stole a motor boat. Aye, it was moored in front of the police station and all, the river police station. And, of course I knew who the owner of the boat was mind, I'd done a lot of work for him, Mickey Hanlan, the shipping butcher
,
 I used to do a lot of work for him. But I never went and asked if I could have a loan of the boat, I just went down and took the boat, I told them, I says, fetch two gallon of petrol with you. And I took the boat, took them all the way to Wryton, to Wryt
on Willows for the day. But - the lads and lasses, I don't suppose they were any better but they weren't as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 mischievous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 in them days, destructive. See, nowadays the kiddies seems - they will damage stuff that - I don't know why, they're only happy if }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 they\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  destroying things nowadays. We didn't used to destroy things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You didn't damage the boat at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, no, took the boat back just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So that was the main difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And - and of course I start courting then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 When you went out where did you go, you went to the dance hall every Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Where else did you go in the evenings when you were about sixteen, seventeen or eighteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Dancing classes, yes. I went to old Mr }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Hutchinson\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  in Charchester Roa
d, just him and his daughter, the dancing class. Very - very refined old chap he was, broad Scotch. And even just a little dancing class like, it was only in his house, he was in his tails and his white gloves. And by God, you - you daren't do a thing wro
ng in that dance hall, not in the hall, in his house, that was his dancing class. And we used to go every night of the week. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Yes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
. Used to cost you a shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Who used to go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 There was a whole crowd of us. The girl I was courting with and there was a lad called Jack Lyle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 People that you worked with were they, these lads?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Aye, lads and - some of them - Jimmy Crawford, he was at pit. Jack Lyle, he was - he was the terror of the gang. He came from a right rough family and - he wa
s never out of trouble. Well he - he was sent to Borstal, he was that bad, he was sent to Borstal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 But he used to get dressed up every night and go to the dancing class did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. Aye. And - I've see - we'd all go to market on a Saturday. 'Cos }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 
Shields}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 had a - a lovely market on a Saturday. Monday and Saturday was market days and - if you were with Jack when you got out of the market you had stuff in your pocket which you hadn't when you went in. You didn't know it was there. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 He'd pinch it and put it in your pockets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 He'd pinch and - he used to pinch that much stuff man, he couldn't put it all in his own. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 There was one Sunday night, went into Joe Marciano's ice cream shop in Ocean Road and - we all used to go in there every Sunda
y night, just for an ice cream and that you know, we didn't spend a lot of time in, and this night Jack comes out and he had a great big basin, must have been a foot in diameter, full of pineapple cubes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 He'd stole off the counter, nobody had seen him take it. He - he - he was a wonderful leader of men and he turned out to be. He was sent to Borstal and he was let out on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 license}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  but - you know - they let them out on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 license}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 , and he was sent to a farm in Burnfield and he was working on a farm at Burnfield an
d - he didn't like it. The discipline was too - a lad that didn't like discipline at all. He - he run away from there and he joined the Army. And - he used to come home on leave often. And - he got in touch with one of the girls - I don't know whether we 
should put this on tape or not -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you make any new friends at this time just after you started work? And if you did how did you make your new friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well I - I - work friends. I took more interest in - men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, not a great lot of women. I was courting and I was a one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 One woman man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Yes. That's one thing I can say. When I actually courted the very first wife - she was still at school when I first started courting her and - I courted 'til we were married. And
 I never troubled with anyone else. But men, I took more interest in union matters and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you ever bring any of your friends home with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You had this special girlfriend, did you have any specials friends among the lads?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Oh yes, we had - what we used to call the clique. That was - there was six lads and six girls. We used to meet every Sunday night at the corner of Ocean Road and John Scott Street. And that used to be our meeting place every Sunday night and - 
we all - we used to go to dances and things like this you know, all kept in a gang and we used - through the week we used to go to these dancing classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 All six of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, All six of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 That was when you were what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Seventeen, eighteen, right up to - well, right up 'til I was married. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your parents know these people in your gang, your clique.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. They knew some of the lads and - me grandmother }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13321278\charrsid8601884 knew}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  the - Norah that I was courting you know. But the rest of the gang
, well they just used to come and call but - they never called - never came to the house actually because they were never made welcome. See me grandmother was an old woman and - she had her set life. Well our life didn't - really compare with hers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did either your grandmother or your father expect to be told where you were going?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I don't think they took that much interest - me father never took any interest in me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So you didn't have to be in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You were twenty-six when you were married, how long had you known your wife then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh - ten year. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How did you meet her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Met her somewhere up North. At a - a whist drive and dance. Stannock Road school. One Saturday night, it was a whist drive and
 dance at the Stannock Road school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 About sixteen I was, I hadn't been working long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 She was a bit younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 She was still at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Thirteen or fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 She'd be about - I was four year older than what she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 South Shields. Yes, her - her people was Russians. Her father was Russian.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Both her father and mother were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Russians}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. Yes. Well, not Russians, Latvians. It wasn't - Russia. Russia wa
s a country of its own that - those days. They were Latvians - come from Latvia.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What was her maiden name then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Mendel. Norah Mendel. Her father was a right Bolshevic. Yes. Very very learned chap. But he - was a funny fellow. I used to go the ho
use - you may as well never have been there. He sat with his bible and nobody dare disturb him. You know, like all day long. He was seafaring. And when he was home he did nothing but - sit and read his Bible. And at night time he used to go to the spiritu
alist church. And - and at home even his wife daren't disturb him when he was reading his Bible. He was a rank communist you know, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Bolshevics}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  as as we called them then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well I don't know about a - whether he was a Christian, to me he wasn't a Christian because a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Christian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  wouldn't act in those ways. He - he professed to be reading his Bible and this but he didn't act in a Christian way. Well that's my opinion mind.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you save up money before getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you get any help from father or your grandmother in setting up house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So it was all your own money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Every - everything that I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Would you have had a couple of thousand in the bank then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh I hadn't that much but I had a good bit of money in the bank.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How long were you engaged for or didn't you bother with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh I don't - we were engaged but were - I - I couldn't say exactly how long we were but I know }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  were engaged.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 More than a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Oh yes. Because - until I got engaged I gave every ha'penny that I worked for to me grandmother. And I got a penny to the shilling pocket money. That's what I got back off her. And when I got engaged I gave her six pound notes and I told her I was going 
on board and she told back over did she expect to keep me on six pounds a week. So I told her straight, I said, well, I can get board anywhere for that in those days which I thought I was doing well by giving her six pounds. Me father was-'t taking that m
uch home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you describe the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 It was a very quick affair, 'cos I got this offer for a job for Canada.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You got this special }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 license}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, we were married in three days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Where were you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Mary\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  church, South Shields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. And we just had the reception at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How many guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Oh - as many as we could get in the house. 'Cos her mother and father had a seamen's boarding house. But only their own nationality, they woul
dn't take any other nationality but Latvians. Yes, only took Latvians in. They had their own Latvian foods and everything in the house. And - the boarders she had they were all like brothers and sisters to her because they were there for years, just the s
a
me - boarders. It was their home actually, they had no home in Latvia and it was just home for them really, they were all - only what we used to call weekly men, on weekly ships running down the coast London and they were calling it their home every week.
 And that was their second home. Well, we were married and - the reception just at home in their - it was big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 we had in South Elder Street and the Latvians, the seamen, kept themselves to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 their selves}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 and all our friends kept themselves to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 their selves}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
. Foreigners. And - we went - we had all day and mind it was a do, eeh. And we went to some friends at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Clevedon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 for our first night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Where's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Clevedon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 It's - on the outskirts of South Shields. And - we went - and went to London the next morning
 on the coach - one of the first coaches that ever run to London. Yes. Orange Brothers. We got -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How long did it take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 We left here at eight o'clock in the morning, we got in ten o'clock at night. Fourteen hours. And I can still remember that jo
urney as though it was yesterday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 It wasn't very comfortable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
No. Oh no, comfortable. It was - it was murder to tell you honest truth. You know when I think of today and - and then, we must have been mad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How much did it cost?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Twelve shillings. It was twelve shillings, I can't remember whether it was single or sixteen shilling return.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Not a lot less than now considering the wages have risen is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you get many wedding presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 None or just a few?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 We got a - a few but nothing to what we should have had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Who did you get presents from then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well I got very few from, me father's family as you may say, me uncles and that - because as I told you me father was the black sheep of the fam
ily and we hadn't - kept up - with them. And - of course - Norah's side, there was only her father and mother with a - we just got odd ones. But the wedding was that quick. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How long did you spend in London on your honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Two weeks. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Where did you stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 In the - what do you call it street, just off High - I can take you back to the same street yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Was it a hotel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. Boarding house in Kings Cross. What was it they call that street? We stopped - what did they cal
l this street, just round the back, I could take you back to the same street, in fact I think a could take you back to the same house if it's still there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Immediately after you married did you go to Canada the next day, after you honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. After the honeymoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Where did you live then before you went to Canada?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well we only had two nights after I came back from our honeymoon.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Then you were off to Canada?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And you lived in Canada two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How old was your wife when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well I was twenty-six she would be twenty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did your wife have a job when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. She - she used to help in the - in the house. She had done that since she left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 When she got married to you did she have any job then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Well after we went to Canada, she had no job in Canada. And then we came back home, we just lived with her mother because I had no house, and we lived with her mother 'til I could get a house or our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So she didn't work outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, she just helped in the house again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You were quite happy with that, you'd rather she was at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes, I - I would never let her go out to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 She didn't have any jobs then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. Never from being married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Do you think that she liked working in the house, being a housewife, doing the kind of work she had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 At times she did, but - until we got a family. She - she longed to go work. Then, and then I told her then I sa
ys, look, I says, when I married you I didn't marry you to work. I says, you've got me and the home to look after. And I wouldn't let her go to work because I thought there was no need for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You were earning plenty of money weren't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How many children did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Were they boys or girls? Were they born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Both - no, one in hospital. The first one was born at home, Chris, he's the eldest and he was born at home. We were married eight year before we had any family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So it was 1934?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Four. And then we went six year before we had the next, Peter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you have any medical help in the home when Christ was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Who came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 The doctor, Doctor Callaghan and the nurse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No. No, they chased me out of the house altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How soon did your wife get out of bed after he was born, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 She was about a fortnight before she got out to the doors but she was up pretty soon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did she stay up for the whole day at the end of that fortnight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Not at first, no, she just got up a little bit at first. But after a fortnight she was going about doing her daily work again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How did you manage when she was in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - from the kiddy 
being born - from Chris being born, I done everything. I changed that bairn, he wouldn't be four hours old and I changed his nappies and everything and I'd never done anything like it in me life. And I - I done everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So you looked after yourself and the baby as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well - her mother was cooking all me meals and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did she come and live with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, we were living with her. See we - we had no home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So she looked after your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Any of your other relations or neighbours help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I had a Mrs Davis, she used to come to help a lot. Mrs Davis, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you have anyone coming in after your wife got up, a nurse or a nanny or anyone to help her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, no. Just her mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How much did you have to do with your children, did you carry on changing nappies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Yes. And - we never went out and left that baby for all her mother was in the house. Would never go out at night anything and leave that child with the mother. I told Norah, I sa
ys, well, it's ours and we look after it and we looked after that lad until he was about four year old, we never had a night out. And - every day - I took that bairn out in a pram, the people used to laugh at me in them days. Yes. But if I wasn't working 
- because was bus driving at the time, I was at the United in them days and I was traveling Newcastle, South Shields. It all depended what shift. If I had any spare time at all I had the bairn out in the pram.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you feed them or bath them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Feed them, everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Play with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Did you get him to sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What happened in the middle of the night when he started crying, did you ever get up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 I always got up. Yes. Always got up. If - if my
 wife had been telling you, she was alive today - for eight month I walked that floor every night, that kiddy couldn't get to sleep. He cried, cried, cried and we tried all kinds of food and - there was one day Mrs Davis came and she says, look, she says,
 give me a tin of Nestles milk and we'll give the bairn a feed of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Nestles}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 milk, which was something it had never had because he'd always had stuff which the doctor - had said he had to have, the proper food. And - and we gave him this Nestles milk this days and he never looked back. Peaceful as anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What was Chris's first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Chris's first job - eeh - he went into Robsons, the wholesale grocers in Newcastle here. He went in the office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 As what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Just an office boy I think he'd be.
 And they taught him to be a rep. Representative you know. And he got a car and - and from there he - he got offered a better - no, Robsons was folded up, that was it, the family, it was a family affair and - and the business folded up and they got him a 
j
ob with Harris, the bacon people you know, Harris's bacon, as a rep. He was with them a long long time. Then he went to Lancashire as a representative for certain areas in Lancashire like. Then from there he - I don't know what happened but he - he packed
 up there and he got another job. I forget now what it was. But it was a big - big firm, one of these big combines, he was a rep. He's still a rep yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 And he's thirty-six now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Chris, aye, he'd be thirty-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about the second child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Peter. He was born in Dilston.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What was his first job? He'd only be thirty now wouldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Peter, I don't think Peter's done anything else but nursing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What kind of nursing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Mental.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Since he left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 He's working in the hospital now is he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes. He's at Wootten General in Lancashire. He's only about twenty minutes from Christ.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 As a cutter again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, no, he was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 salvage}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What kind of a job's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well when - when an area's 
what you call worked out and there's no coal left they take out all - whatever they can get. The old timber, chocks they used to keep the roof up with you know, pipes that conduct the air through. You bring all those back, you take the timber out and just
 let the place fall it. It's a very dangerous job. He - he's lucky to be alive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Is it a well paid job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I wouldn't say it's a well paid job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How did it compare with being a cutter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh, it's nowhere near. No. Well when Bill went back
 he couldn't get back cutting. See, because electric machines was all coming in. By that and - and Bill had severed his connection with the union as well, see when he left - he left the union and he was lucky actually get back in the pit, as a detail man,
 that's what they call when you go back as salvage men, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 detail}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884  men. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3558474\charrsid8601884 Detail}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 It covers what kind of jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
Anything. But you're only on a - a daily wage. You're - you're not a piece worker or anything. And you can be given any kind of job which -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So it refers to any kind of labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, just labourer, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Can you get the sack from day to day as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh yes. By heavens. Chase you out as soon as looking at you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 He stayed in that 'til he retired did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 He's in there 'til forty - 'til sixty-five. He's still living in South Shields yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 You didn't have any daughters did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, I just had two sons.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Does he enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well he must do. Because he's never wanted to do anything else. He's as high up as he possibly can get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What is his official title of his job, his grade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Oh - chief nurse or something. I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What about your brothers, what jobs have they had? Your brother that's younger than you, he started in the pit didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 What }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13321278\charrsid8601884 has}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 he done since then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Well he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How old was he when he started in the pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Fourteen, the same as me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 How much younger than you was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Fourteen month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So he started about 1915?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 Yes, fourteen m
onth and - he came into the pit the same as me. In - he worked right up until '26 strike, I got him on - on the machines the same as me, I got him on cutting the same as me. He never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 So he was as rich as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 No, he was like me father. He wasn't as bad as me father but he liked his beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12721239 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 After '26 what did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13512717 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
After the '26 strike I went to Canada and he was left at home there. Well, me father got him a job in Redheads, in the shipyard. Just labouring, see, 'cos he couldn't do anything else, he wasn't a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13321278\charrsid8601884  craftsman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1460185\charrsid8601884 
 And - he laboured there for ph a lot of years. I think it must have been about fifteen to twenty years he was in Redhead. He went back into pit and he finished up, he was working clearing the pit.
\par }}